  "root_text": {
    "sn35.33:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 35.33–42 ",
    "sn35.33:0.2": "4. Jātidhammavagga ",
    "sn35.33:0.3": "Jātidhammādisuttadasaka ",
    "sn35.33:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn35.33:1.2": "Tatra kho …pe… ",
    "sn35.33:1.3": "“sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, jātidhammaṁ. ",
    "sn35.33:1.4": "Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṁ jātidhammaṁ? ",
    "sn35.33:1.5": "Cakkhu, bhikkhave, jātidhammaṁ. ",
    "sn35.33:1.6": "Rūpā … ",
    "sn35.33:1.7": "cakkhuviññāṇaṁ … ",
    "sn35.33:1.8": "cakkhusamphasso jātidhammo. ",
    "sn35.33:1.9": "Yampidaṁ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṁ sukhaṁ vā dukkhaṁ vā adukkhamasukhaṁ vā tampi jātidhammaṁ …pe… ",
    "sn35.33:1.10": "jivhā … ",
    "sn35.33:1.11": "rasā … ",
    "sn35.33:1.12": "jivhāviññāṇaṁ … ",
    "sn35.33:1.13": "jivhāsamphasso … ",
    "sn35.33:1.14": "yampidaṁ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṁ sukhaṁ vā dukkhaṁ vā adukkhamasukhaṁ vā tampi jātidhammaṁ. ",
    "sn35.33:1.15": "Kāyo …pe… ",
    "sn35.33:1.16": "mano jātidhammo, dhammā jātidhammā, manoviññāṇaṁ jātidhammaṁ, manosamphasso jātidhammo. ",
    "sn35.33:1.17": "Yampidaṁ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṁ sukhaṁ vā dukkhaṁ vā adukkhamasukhaṁ vā tampi jātidhammaṁ. ",
    "sn35.33:1.18": "Evaṁ passaṁ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi … cakkhuviññāṇepi … cakkhusamphassepi …pe… ",
    "sn35.33:1.19": "nāparaṁ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti. ",
    "sn35.33:1.20": "Paṭhamaṁ. ",
    "sn35.34:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, jarādhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.34:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.34:1.3": "Dutiyaṁ. ",
    "sn35.35:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, byādhidhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.35:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.35:1.3": "Tatiyaṁ. ",
    "sn35.36:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, maraṇadhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.36:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.36:1.3": "Catutthaṁ. ",
    "sn35.37:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, sokadhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.37:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.37:1.3": "Pañcamaṁ. ",
    "sn35.38:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, saṅkilesikadhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.38:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.38:1.3": "Chaṭṭhaṁ. ",
    "sn35.39:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, khayadhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.39:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.39:1.3": "Sattamaṁ. ",
    "sn35.40:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, vayadhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.40:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.40:1.3": "Aṭṭhamaṁ. ",
    "sn35.41:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, samudayadhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.41:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.41:1.3": "Navamaṁ. ",
    "sn35.42:1.1": "“Sabbaṁ, bhikkhave, nirodhadhammaṁ … ",
    "sn35.42:1.2": "saṅkhittaṁ. ",
    "sn35.42:1.3": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "sn35.42:1.4": "Jātidhammavaggo catuttho. ",
    "sn35.42:2.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn35.42:2.1": "Jātijarābyādhimaraṇaṁ, ",
    "sn35.42:2.2": "Soko ca saṅkilesikaṁ; ",
    "sn35.42:2.3": "Khayavayasamudayaṁ, ",
    "sn35.42:2.4": "Nirodhadhammena te dasāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn35.33:0.1": "Linked Discourses 35.33–42 ",
    "sn35.33:0.2": "4. Liable to Be Reborn ",
    "sn35.33:0.3": "Ten on Liable to Be Reborn, Etc. ",
    "sn35.33:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn35.33:1.2": "",
    "sn35.33:1.3": "“Mendicants, all is liable to be reborn. ",
    "sn35.33:1.4": "And what is the all that is liable to be reborn? ",
    "sn35.33:1.5": "The eye, ",
    "sn35.33:1.6": "sights, ",
    "sn35.33:1.7": "eye consciousness, ",
    "sn35.33:1.8": "and eye contact are liable to be reborn. ",
    "sn35.33:1.9": "And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises dependent on eye contact is also liable to be reborn. ",
    "sn35.33:1.10": "The ear … nose … tongue … ",
    "sn35.33:1.11": "",
    "sn35.33:1.12": "",
    "sn35.33:1.13": "",
    "sn35.33:1.14": "",
    "sn35.33:1.15": "body … ",
    "sn35.33:1.16": "The mind, ideas, mind consciousness, and mind contact are liable to be reborn. ",
    "sn35.33:1.17": "And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises dependent on mind contact is also liable to be reborn. ",
    "sn35.33:1.18": "Seeing this a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned … ",
    "sn35.33:1.19": "They understand: ‘… there is nothing further for this place.’” ",
    "sn35.33:1.20": "",
    "sn35.34:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to grow old. …” ",
    "sn35.34:1.2": "",
    "sn35.34:1.3": "",
    "sn35.35:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to fall sick. …” ",
    "sn35.35:1.2": "",
    "sn35.35:1.3": "",
    "sn35.36:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to die. …” ",
    "sn35.36:1.2": "",
    "sn35.36:1.3": "",
    "sn35.37:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to sorrow. …” ",
    "sn35.37:1.2": "",
    "sn35.37:1.3": "",
    "sn35.38:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to corruption. …” ",
    "sn35.38:1.2": "",
    "sn35.38:1.3": "",
    "sn35.39:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to end. …” ",
    "sn35.39:1.2": "",
    "sn35.39:1.3": "",
    "sn35.40:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to fall. …” ",
    "sn35.40:1.2": "",
    "sn35.40:1.3": "",
    "sn35.41:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to originate. …” ",
    "sn35.41:1.2": "",
    "sn35.41:1.3": "",
    "sn35.42:1.1": "“Mendicants, all is liable to cease. …” ",
    "sn35.42:1.2": "",
    "sn35.42:1.3": "",
    "sn35.42:1.4": "",
    "sn35.42:2.1": "",
    "sn35.42:2.2": "",
